comments: Robinson-Earl (OKC) extends his chest and delivers body contact to Jokic (DEN), which affects his SQBR during the drive.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) comes across Pokusevski's (OKC) left wrist in order to dislodge the ball on the layup attempt.
Gordon (DEN) is whistled for disconcerting Pokusevski (OKC) during his free throw attempt.
Dort (OKC) takes a step toward Brown (DEN), causing them to come together on the perimeter, and the contact is marginal.
Williams (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) goes to, not through, Brown's (DEN) space and marginal contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander spins away during the drive.
Earl-Robinson (OKC) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage in the post, and the contact is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and does not deliver contact.
Pokusevski (OKC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Pokusevski (OKC) contests the layup attempt and marginal body contact occurs with Gordon (DEN) after the release.
Jokic (DEN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Jokic (DEN) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs at the end of Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) drive.
Cancar (DEN) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Williams' (OKC) layup attempt.
Williams (OKC) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Jokic (DEN) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Caldwell-Pope (DEN) engage and disengage off-ball, and Caldwell-Pope momentarily loses his balance.
Williams (OKC) and Gordon (DEN) engage in pursuit of the loose ball, and marginal arm contact occurs during the rebound.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) come together in transition, and marginal body contact occurs.
The game clock expires prior to any potential contact by Brown (DEN) during Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) drive.
Gordon (DEN) and Williams (OKC) engage in marginal arm-to-arm contact during the rebound.
Jokic (DEN) and Williams (OKC) engage under the basket during the long rebound and separate, and the contact is marginal.
Dort (OKC) swipes and grazes Cancar's (DEN) body during his layup attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) brings his left arm up and through, causing contact to occur with Joe's (OKC) head, which dislodges him.
Cancar (DEN) slides laterally into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and delivers body contact, which affects his SQBR.
Dort (OKC) and Jokic (DEN) engage in incidental contact as both players move toward the loose ball.
Brown (DEN) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) and Pokusevski (OKC) tie the ball up in Brown's (DEN) hands and incidental arm contact occurs.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Gordon (DEN) is in the lane for three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) swipes down and initiates contact with Dort's (OKC) left arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) commits a take foul on Caldwell-Pope (DEN).
Williams (OKC) wraps his left arm around Jokic's (DEN) back prior to dislodging the ball away.
Gordon (DEN) rests a slight hand on Giddey's (OKC) side and retracts it as he elevates, causing marginal body contact to occur during the driving shot attempt.
Gordon (DEN) legally contests Giddey's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
